ig functions & return types","user":{"login":"Seelengrab","id":11753998,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNzUzOTk4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/11753998?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab","html_url":"https://github.com/Seelengrab","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Seelengrab/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"This documents the failure cases of various trigonometric functions provided in Base, but is not exhaustive. In particular, there are still undocumented failure cases of the versions of these functions taking matrices, but this can be added at a later date. The failure cases where found with PropCheck.jl, checking if the property `x -> f(x) isa T` for the functions `f` in question and the types `(Int8, Int16, Int32, Int64, Float16, Float32, Float64)` holds (i.e., doesn't error and returns `true`). I can give a script reproducing the failures if requested.

