{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288","id":1773415769,"node_id":"I_kwDOABkWpM5ptC1Z","number":50288,"title":"Should we add a keyword to sort missing values as small  `sort!(v, missingssmallest=true)`?","user":{"login":"LilithHafner","id":60898866,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYwODk4ODY2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/60898866?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner","html_url":"https://github.com/LilithHafner","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LilithHafner/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":97639,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw5NzYzOQ==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/speculative","name":"speculative","color":"999999","default":false,"description":"Whether the change will be implemented is speculative"},{"id":437820724,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0Mzc4MjA3MjQ=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/missing%20data","name":"missing data","color":"d4c5f9","default":false,"description":"Base.missing and related functionality"},{"id":909268321,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw5MDkyNjgzMjE=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/feature","name":"feature","color":"5664ff","default":false,"description":"Indicates new feature / enhancement requests"},{"id":4342669890,"node_id":"LA_kwDOABkWpM8AAAABAtfiQg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/sort","name":"sort","color":"fef2c0","default":false,"description":"Put things in order"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2023-06-25T18:09:15Z","updated_at":"2023-06-25T20:39:42Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Right now, missing values are always sorted as the largest value. By default, this puts them at the end, just past the highest non-missing value. When sorting with `rev=true`, this puts them at the beginning, just before the highest non-missing value. Do we want a way to order them just past the smallest value?

_originally posted by @chris-b1 in https://github.com/JuliaData/DataFrames.jl/issues/2267_

Adding a subtype of `Ordering` that accomplishes this can be done in a package. Adding a keyword to conveniently construct those orderings in general would need to be implemented in Base (and therefore all the machinery would need to be in Base).","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1606255937","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288#issuecomment-1606255937","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/50288","id":1606255937,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM5fvYVB","user":{"login":"nalimilan","id":1120448,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMjA0NDg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1120448?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan","html_url":"https://github.com/nalimilan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-06-25T20:39:42Z","updated_at":"2023-06-25T20:39:42Z","author_association":"MEMBER","body":"As discussed at https://github.com/JuliaData/DataFrames.jl/issues/2267 and https://github.com/JuliaData/Missings.jl/issues/142, I don't think we need a specific keyword argument for this, as a syntax like `lt=missingisless` is convenient enough. But I'm not sure whether it would be possible to implement efficient algorithms for this custom ordering from outside Base given that `missing` and `isless` are special-cased in a few places.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1606255937/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

{"action":"opened","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/49301","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/49301/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/49301/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/49301/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/49301","id":1659896421,"node_id":"I_kwDOABkWpM5i8AJl","number":49301,"title":"Summation loop does not use SIMD with `Union{Int8, Missing}` vector and `ismissing`","user":{"login":"nalimilan","id":1120448,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMjA0NDg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1120448?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan","html_url":"https://github.com/nalimilan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nalimilan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":115858,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMTU4NTg=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/performance","name":"performance","color":"d7e102","default":false,"description":"Must go faster"},{"id":437820724,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0Mzc4MjA3MjQ=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/missing%20data","name":"missing data","color":"d4c5f9","default":false,"description":"Base.missing and related functionality"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2023-04-09T14:36:10Z","updated_at":"2023-04-09T14:36:10Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"The following simple sum does not use SIMD instructions when eltype is `Union{Int8, Missing}`, but it does with `Union{Int16, Missing}` (and `Int32`, `Int64`). Due to this, summing `Int16` values is faster than summing `Int8` values.

The problem disappears when replacing `!ismissing(ai)` with `ai !== missing`.

I have tried starting Julia with `JULIA_LLVM_ARGS="-pass-remarks-analysis=loop-vectorize -pass-remarks=vector"`, but surprisingly no message is printed for `mysum(A8)` that would indicate success or failure to vectorize.

This blocks PR https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44407.

```julia
function mysum(A::AbstractArray)
    s = Base.add_sum(zero(eltype(A)), zero(eltype(A)))
    @simd for i in 1:length(A)
        @inbounds ai = A[i]
        if !ismissing(ai)
            s = Base.add_sum(s, ai)
        end
    end
    return s
end

using BenchmarkTools
A8 = Vector{Union{Int8, Missing}}(rand(Int8, 10_000));
A16 = Vector{Union{Int16, Missing}}(A8);

julia> @btime mysum(A8);
  5.109 μs (1 allocation: 16 bytes)

julia> @btime mysum(A16);
  1.858 μs (1 allocation: 16 bytes)
```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/49301/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/49301/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}}

